<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TVM3.4.8">
<l>oḷimaṇi vaṇṇa ṉeṉkō voruvaṉeṉ ṟētta niṉṟa</l>
<l>naḷirmatic caṭaiya ṉeṉkō nāṉmukak kaṭavu ḷeṉkō</l>
<l>vaḷimakiḻn tulaka mellām paṭaittavai yētta niṉṟa</l>
<l>kaḷimalart tuḷava ṉemmāṉ kaṇṇaṉai māya ṉaiyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Will I say “the one of bright sapphire colour”? Will I say “he in whose matted hair is the cool moon</l>
<l>who stands as they praise [him] as one”? Will I say “the four-facted god”?</l>
<l>– to him with nectar-blossom tulsi, lord, Kṛṣṇa, the trickster</l> 
<l>who stands while while they praise [him] for all the worlds he created, rejoicing in [his] care.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
